# Color system

Source of truth: `src/styles/colors.css`. Agent-readable overview + when-to-use: `DESIGN.md` ┬ž2. Tailwind utilities in `src/index.css` (`@theme` + component classes).

## Three layers

1. **Primitives** (`--palette-*`) ÔÇö raw palette. **`--palette-white`** / **`--palette-black`** alias neutral-0 / neutral-950. Never use hex in components.
2. **UI foundations** (`--app-bg`, `--app-surface-*`, `--app-border-*`, `--app-text-*`, `--app-fill-*`, `--app-frost-surface`, `--app-progress-*`) ÔÇö structural UI. Prefer Tailwind utilities.

**Light Ôćö dark:** when a spec says ÔÇťwhite @ 90%ÔÇŁ or ÔÇťblackÔÇŁ, define `--app-*` in `:root` + `.dark` (whiteÔćöblack inversion) ÔÇö never hardcode `bg-white` / `bg-black` on themed surfaces.
3. **Feature** (`--app-chrome-*`, plus any product-specific tokens you add) ÔÇö feature presentation only, referencing Layer 2.

Light values on `:root`; dark overrides in `.dark`. Default theme is **light** (`uiStore.theme`).

## Surfaces (when to use)

| Utility | Use |
|---|-----|
| `bg-background` | App shell, sidebar, content panel backdrop (**bg**) |
| `bg-surface-1` | Workspace card, primary content, cards, table body rows |
| `bg-surface-2` | Subtle bands ÔÇö table headers, section chrome (neutral-50 light) |
| `bg-surface-3` | Inset wells ÔÇö inputs, metric cards, muted panels (neutral-100 light) |

Legacy aliases still work: `bg-content` / `bg-card` Ôćĺ surface-1; `bg-muted` / `bg-input` Ôćĺ surface-3; `bg-popover` Ôćĺ surface-1 (elevated via shadow).

## Borders Ôćĺ inset edges

Structural edges use **inset shadow** (not `border`) so they read on any fill:

| Utility | Use |
|---|-----|
| `inset-edge-ring` + `inset-edge-ring-full` | Cards, inputs, buttons, popovers ÔÇö `inset 0 0 0 1px` on the element |
| `inset-edge` + `inset-edge-full` | Layered surfaces ÔÇö shadow on `::after` overlay |
| `inset-edge-ring-b` / `inset-edge-b` | Single-edge dividers |
| `inset-edge-strong` | Dialogs, sheets (was `border-border-strong`) |
| `inset-edge-soft` | Muted containers (was `border-border/50`) |
| `inset-edge-hover` | Interactive edge (was `hover:border-border-hover`) |
| `inset-edge-chrome` + `inset-edge-chrome-hover` | Toolbar outline controls |
| `bg-frost-surface` | Frosted panels (white 90% light Ôćĺ black 90% dark) + `backdrop-blur` |
| `bg-progress-track` / `bg-progress-fill` | Progress bars (neutral-200 / black light Ôćĺ neutral-800 / white dark) |

When the user specifies **white @ opacity** or **black** for UI chrome, add or use an `--app-*` token with `:root` + `.dark` overrides ÔÇö do not hardcode `bg-white` / `bg-black` in components.

## Do this

- **Text**: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-on-canvas` (workspace alias).
- **Hover fills**: `bg-fill-hover`, `bg-fill-selected`, `bg-accent/40` for menus/rows.
- **Toolbar on page headers**: `text-chrome-fg`, `pageChrome` button variants.
- **Status**: `text-status-*` on icons/labels only ÔÇö not structural borders.
- **New tokens**: primitive Ôćĺ `--app-*` in `colors.css` Ôćĺ `@theme` Ôćĺ utility Ôćĺ `DESIGN.md` table.
- **Never** put `shadow-none` on elements that use `inset-edge-ring*` ÔÇö it clears the inset ÔÇťborderÔÇŁ.

## Avoid this

- Raw hex, `--palette-*`, `text-white`, scattered `dark:` pairs.
- Status colors on structural borders or app chrome.
- Duplicating feature colors in TS ÔÇö extend `colors.css`.

## Quick reference

```tsx
// App shell
className="bg-background" // bg
className="bg-surface-1 inset-edge-ring inset-edge-ring-full" // workspace card

// Interactive edge
className="inset-edge-ring inset-edge-ring-full inset-edge-hover transition-surface duration-150 ease-hover"

// Row hover
className="hover:bg-fill-hover"
```

Boot skeleton in `index.html` mirrors `--app-bg` / `--app-surface-1` until CSS loads.
